'''Amanda Lucas''' (born [[July 15]], [[1981]]) is the eldest adopted daughter of [[George Lucas]]. She has played a minor role in all three [[Prequel trilogy|prequel films]]. In the animated television series ''[[Star Wars: The Clone Wars]]'', the character [[Che Amanwe Papanoida]] is based on her.

She has since gone on to participate in [[Wikipedia:mixed martial arts|mixed martial arts]], debuting on 31 May 2008 in a fight against [[Wikipedia:New Zealand|New Zealand]] [[Wikipedia:kickboxing|kickboxing]] champion Nicole Kavanah.<ref name="The force was not with the Princess of Pain">{{WebCite|url=http://www.tv3.co.nz/News/Story/tabid/209/articleID/57904/cat/41/Default.aspx|text=The force was not with the 'Princess of Pain'|archivedate=20080606054833}}</ref> She is married to [[Jason Hallikainen]],<ref name="espn">{{WebCite|url=http://espn.go.com/espn/page2/story/_/id/7676351/amanda-lucas-daughter-george-lucas-making-name-self-mma|text="Amanda Lucas using her Force" - ESPN.com|archivedate=20120313220946}}</ref> who played [[Són Halliikeenovich|an extra]] alongside her character, [[Terr Taneel]], during the [[Galaxies Opera House|opera house]] scene in [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|''Revenge of the Sith'']].<ref>''[[The Making of Star Wars Revenge of the Sith]]'', p. 194</ref> The couple's first son, Felix, was born in [[2014]].<ref name="Felix">{{Twitter|amandalucasmma|status/487450660929941505|[[Amanda Lucas]]|quote=Baby Felix has arrived & is healthy!|archivedate=20200807201524}}</ref>

